# Dataset Format

The training script expects CSV or Excel files containing the following columns:

text ID Mean_Pupil_Size Blink_Freq Gaze_Disp Label 

Example:

| ID | Mean_Pupil_Size | Blink_Freq | Gaze_Disp | Label |
|----|----|----|----|----|
| 1 | 6.45 | 0.34 | 18.2 | 0 |
| 1 | 6.29 | 0.41 | 15.1 | 0 |
| 1 | 5.98 | 0.62 | 9.8 | 1 |

Where:

- Mean_Pupil_Size = average pupil radius over a time window
- Blink_Freq = blink frequency
- Gaze_Disp = gaze movement/displacement
- Label = attention state

---

# Experimental Setup

Participants complete two conditions:

## External Attention Condition

Participants watch engaging content intended to maintain focus.

Examples:

- Interesting videos
- Puzzles
- Interactive tasks

Expected behaviour:

- Higher gaze movement
- Lower blink frequency
- Stronger responses to external stimuli

---

## Internal Attention Condition

Participants watch boring or incomprehensible content while being encouraged to think internally.

Examples:

- Boring lectures
- Foreign-language videos
- Mind-wandering tasks

Expected behaviour:

- Reduced gaze movement
- Increased blinking
- Reduced responsiveness to external stimuli

---

# Machine Learning Pipeline

The project uses:

- Logistic Regression
- Random Forest
- Support Vector Machine (SVM)

