---

# What Happens During Live Prediction?

The webcam opens.

For every frame:

### Blink Detection

The system calculates:

text Eye Aspect Ratio (EAR) 

to detect blinks.

---

### Gaze Tracking

The iris centre is tracked using:

text MediaPipe Face Mesh 

The system calculates:

text gaze_x gaze_y gaze_displacement 

---

### Pupil Detection

The dark pupil region is detected using image thresholding.

The system estimates:

text pupil radius 

and determines whether it is:

text Increasing Decreasing Stable 

---

# Live Feature Aggregation

The model was trained on aggregated data rather than individual frames.

Therefore:

Every 30 seconds the system computes:

text Mean_Pupil_Size Blink_Freq Gaze_Disp 

from the live stream.

---

# Prediction Process

The 30-second feature vector is passed to the trained model:

text Mean_Pupil_Size Blink_Freq Gaze_Disp 

The model predicts:

text Focused 

or

text Daydreaming 

